*Plans To Synergise With FG For Enhanced Development MAKURDI â€“ Terwase Orbunde, former Chief of Staff (Cos) to Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue state said the state has lost so much in the last four years for being in the opposition. He argued that the state in the first four years of the Ortom administration made tremendous progress because it identified with the FG. -Advertisement- Orbunde who is a gubernatorial aspirant on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state said if elected Governor in 2023, he would synergise with the Federal Government (FG) for enhanced development in the state. He made this known while interfacing with the leadership of the APC in the state over his aspiration to be Governor of the state in 2023 at the party secretariat in Makurdi last weekend. Orbunde also attributed achievements of previous administrations, including the first civilian Governor of the state, Aper Aku to his synergy with the FG. The former CoS who stated that his area of priority if elected Governor would include enhanced security, by encouraging clustered settlement patterns, which would in turn boost security in the state. He further stated that as he boosts security in Benue, it would bring about a multiplier effect in the area of Agricultural mechanisation, make the state a hub of protein and evolve policies for solid minerals development. POLL Orbunde appealed to leaders and members of the APC not to entertain fears about his entry assuring that as a game changer, his coming has brought value addition to the fortunes of APC in the state. State APC Chairman, Comrade Austin Agada, represented by State Secretary, Rt. Hon. Paul Ibiam, stated that the party appreciated Orbunde for his voluntary choice to canvass his governorship ambition on its platform. He said the party had given Orbunde unrestricted and unhindered access to the APC family throughout the state as he goes in pursuit of his gubernatorial ambition.